    while (!shell.isDisposed ()) {
        if (!display.readAndDispatch ()) display.sleep ();
    }
    display.dispose ();

}
Not sure we should fix this.  We are using TVS_FULLROWSELECT and this is what 
Windows is doing (even though it is unwanted).
Spoke too soon, let me look into it some more ...
