Bug.WithStack:
Display the test.cpp file in the DOM AST View.  Then use F3 on printf to 
navigate to stdio.h.  Select the printf that is highlighted in stdio.h and 
perform "Show IASTNode in DOM AST".

Then close Eclipse and restart it.  The DOM AST View will be broken and won't 
be usable unless it is closed and then Eclipse is restarted.

// test.cpp:
#include <stdio.h>

int main(int argc, char **argv) {
	printf("testing");
}
Created attachment 25048
fix for this PR
Can you take a look at this when you get a minute?
All DOM/AST Viewer bugs can be marked for 3.0 since they serve as tests (low risk).
Applied.

